==English==
===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /mɔː(r)dənt/

====Homophones====
*[[mordent]]

===Adjective===
'''mordant''' (''[[comparative]]'' '''more mordant''', ''[[superlative]]'' '''most mordant''')

#Biting; caustic; sarcastic; keen; severe.
#Serving to fix colors when [[dye]]ing.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1964''': In dyeing two mediums are required, the colouring matter and the mordant which fixes the dye in the wool. &mdash; L.F. Salzman, ''English Industries of the Middle Ages'', p. 208.

===Noun===
'''mordant''' (''plural'' '''mordants''')
#A substance that [[fix]]es [[dye]].

===Transitive verb===
'''mordant''' (mordanted, mordanting)
#To subject to the action of, or [[imbue]] with, a mordant.
#:''mordant goods for dyeing''

